Figure 7.2

Read in data and fit linear models first, then generate plot

breit <- read.csv("../data/breit.csv")
head(breit,10)
breit.aov<-aov(mda~site*season, data=breit)
#Transform response to logs & refit model with log data
breit$lmda<- log10(breit$mda) 
lbreit.aov<-aov(lmda~site*season, data=breit)
breit2<-summarySE(data=breit,measurevar="mda", groupvars=c("site", "season"))

#Interaction plot

p5<-ggplot(breit2, aes(x = site, y = mda, fill = season)) +
  geom_errorbar(aes(ymin = mda-se, ymax = mda+se), width=0, position = position_dodge(width=0.6)) +
  geom_bar(stat = "identity", width=.6, position = position_dodge(width=0.6), color=lc) +
  scale_fill_grey(start=fs, end=fe, na.value = "red",labels = c("March", "September"))+
  scale_y_continuous(expand = c(0,0))+
  scale_x_discrete(labels = str_wrap(c("Les Palles", "Loix", "Minimes", "Port Neuf"), width = 7))+
  labs(x = NULL, y = "MDA")+
    theme_qk()+
    theme(
    axis.text.x = element_text(colour = "black", size=8),
    legend.key.size = unit(0.35, 'cm'), #change legend key size
#        legend.key.height = unit(1, 'cm'), #change legend key height
#        legend.key.width = unit(1, 'cm'), #change legend key width
 #       legend.title = element_text(size=14), #change legend title font size
#        legend.text = element_text(size=10)) #change legend text font size
  legend.position = "right",
  legend.title = element_blank(),
  legend.text=element_text(size=7),
  )
#Residual plots
p1<-ggplot(breit.aov, aes(x = breit.aov$fitted.values, y = breit.aov$residuals)) +
  geom_point(color=sc) +
  labs(x = "Predicted", y = "Residuals"
       )+
#  scale_x_continuous(breaks=pretty_breaks(n=3))+
  theme_qk()+
  ggtitle("Untransformed")+
  theme(plot.title=element_text(size=8, hjust=0.5))
p3<-ggplot(lbreit.aov, aes(x = lbreit.aov$fitted.values, y = lbreit.aov$residuals)) +
  geom_point(color=sc) +
  labs(x = "Predicted", y = NULL)+
  scale_x_continuous(breaks=pretty_breaks(n=3))+
  theme_qk()+
  ggtitle("Log transformed")+
  theme(plot.title=element_text(size=8, hjust=0.5))
F7_2<-p1+p3+p5+plot_layout(widths = c(1,1,2))
F7_2

#Add colour to interaction plot
F7_2_col<-F7_2 + scale_fill_uchicago(labels = c("March", "September"))

Figure 7.6

longport <- read.csv("../data/longport.csv")
longport.aov <- aov(days~site*salinity*scale, data=longport)
#Residual plot
p1<-ggplot(longport.aov, aes(x = longport.aov$fitted.values, y = longport.aov$residuals)) +
geom_point(color=sc, alpha=0.5) +
labs(x = "Predicted", y = "Residuals"
)+
  theme_qk()
#Interaction plots
#Use emmeans to make file of means and se
emm1<-emmeans(longport.aov, ~site|salinity|scale)
emm2<-as.data.frame(emm1)

#Separate interaction plots for N and S
#Means and error bars
#Use filter to subset data for ggplot
emm3<-filter(emm2, site=="North")
pd=position_dodge(width=0)
p2<-ggplot(emm3,aes(x=salinity,y=emmean,shape=scale, group=scale, color=scale))+
  geom_point(position=pd,aes(shape=scale), size=3,show.legend = FALSE)+
  geom_errorbar(aes(ymin = emmean-SE, ymax = emmean+SE), width=0, position = pd,show.legend = FALSE)+
  geom_line(aes(color=scale), position=pd, size=ls, show.legend = FALSE)+
  scale_color_grey(start=0.2, end=0.8, labels = c("No scale", "Scale"))+
  labs(x = "Salinity", y = "Days to senescence", title="North Site"
       )+
  ylim(50,150)+
  scale_x_discrete(labels=c("Ambient", "Enhanced"))+
  theme_qk()+
  theme(
    axis.text.x = element_text(color="black"),
    legend.position = c(.9, .50),
  legend.justification = c("right", "top"),
  legend.box.just = "right",
  legend.margin = margin(6, 6, 6, 6),
  plot.title = element_text(hjust=0.5),
  legend.title=element_blank()
)
#Now S site
emm4<-filter(emm2, site=="South")
pd=position_dodge(width=0)
p3<-ggplot(emm4, aes(x=salinity,y=emmean,shape=scale, group=scale, color=scale))+
  geom_point(position=pd,aes(shape=scale), size=3,show.legend = FALSE)+
  geom_errorbar(aes(ymin = emmean-SE, ymax = emmean+SE), width=0, position = pd,show.legend = FALSE)+
  geom_line(aes(color=scale), position=pd, size=ls, show.legend = FALSE)+
  scale_color_grey(start=0.2, end=0.8, labels = c("No scale", "Scale"))+
  labs(x = "Salinity", y = "Days to senescence", title="South Site"
       )+
  ylim(50,150)+
  scale_x_discrete(labels=c("Ambient", "Enhanced"))+
  theme_qk()+
  theme(
    axis.text.x = element_text(color="black"),
    legend.position = c(.9, .50),
  legend.justification = c("right", "top"),
  legend.box.just = "right",
  legend.margin = margin(6, 6, 6, 6),
  plot.title = element_text(hjust=0.5),
  legend.title=element_blank()
)

Get data and fit models first, then generate plots

Panel of 4 residual plots, 2 dependent variables, raw and transformed

p1<-ggplot(shawshack1.aov, aes(x = shawshack1.aov$fitted.values, y = shawshack1.aov$residuals)) +
  geom_point(color=sc, alpha=0.5) +
  theme(
    axis.text = element_blank(),
    axis.line = element_line(color = sc),
    axis.ticks = element_blank(),
    plot.title = element_text(hjust=0.5, size=8)
        )+labs(x = NULL, y = NULL, title="Seeds, Raw"
       )
p2<-ggplot(shawshack2.aov, aes(x = shawshack2.aov$fitted.values, y = shawshack2.aov$residuals)) +
  geom_point(color=sc, alpha=0.5) +
  theme(
    axis.text = element_blank(),
    axis.line = element_line(color = sc),
    axis.ticks = element_blank(),
    plot.title = element_text(hjust=0.5, size=8)
        )+labs(x = NULL, y = NULL, title="Growth, Raw"
       )
p3<-ggplot(shawshack1.aov, aes(x = shawshack3.aov$fitted.values, y = shawshack3.aov$residuals)) +
  geom_point(color=sc, alpha=0.5) +
  theme(
    axis.text = element_blank(),
    axis.line = element_line(color = sc),
    axis.ticks = element_blank(),
    plot.title = element_text(hjust=0.5, size=8)
        )+labs(x = NULL, y = NULL, title="Seeds, Log-transformed"
       )
p4<-ggplot(shawshack1.aov, aes(x = shawshack4.aov$fitted.values, y = shawshack4.aov$residuals)) +
  geom_point(color=sc, alpha=.5) +
   theme(
    axis.text = element_blank(),
    axis.line = element_line(color = sc),
    axis.ticks = element_blank(),
    plot.title = element_text(hjust=0.5, size=8)
        )+labs(x = NULL, y = NULL, title="Growth, Log-transformed"
       )
F7_7<-p1+p2+p3+p4+plot_layout(ncol=2)&theme_qk()
